&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rotational Preceptorship Midwife (band 5 AfC for first 6 months)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our rotational posts offer excellent all round experience in a progressive environment, with the potential for individuals to develop a full range of midwifery skills; over 11 months you will work in all areas of the service including high and low risk, developing the skills to ensure you become the midwife that you aspire to be!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Offering:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An innovative, personalised, start to your midwifery career in a friendly, non-judgmental environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A carefully planned preceptorship with protected learning time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The possibility of accreditation at level 7 and the opportunity to work towards an MSc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The chance to consolidate your midwifery practice within an excellent team with dedicated clinical support for preceptees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rated “Good” by CQC in October 2019&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improved facilities courtesy of Barts Charity, including a new, state of the art birth centre and research centre&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A confirmed site of redevelopment with a completely new hospital being pledged by 2026&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For More Information or to arrange a visit please contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rosie Doman, Clinical Educator: rosie.doman@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Rita Osayimwen, Interim Professional Development Midwife &amp; Post Preceptorship Link Midwife on r.osayimwen@nhs.net or Michelle Gladstein, Maternity Recruitment Lead on michelle.gladstein@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
